00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:20.000
 Warm greetings. Welcome, everyone. Welcome. So we'll begin as we usually begin, which is

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:26.200
 to very intentionally and consciously awaken our natural goodness, our bodhicitta, the heart-mind

00:00:26.200 --> 00:00:31.760
 of enlightenment. So we'll just brightly turn that on with full of confidence and joy and

00:00:31.760 --> 00:00:37.960
 enthusiasm, and then we'll really kind of orient this time together, that it'll be of

00:00:37.960 --> 00:00:42.800
 ultimate benefit for all beings, both bringing them immediate happiness in all ways right

00:00:42.800 --> 00:00:49.360
 now, and then also very soon the enlightenment and freedom from all suffering and its causes

00:00:49.360 --> 00:01:16.440
 as well. So we'll just turn on bodhicitta right now. Thanks so much. So early homage

00:01:16.440 --> 00:01:21.040
 to the lineage masters, homage to Buddhist Sakimuni, homage to Guru Rinpoche, homage to

00:01:21.040 --> 00:01:28.400
 this stainless golden mountain range of pristine lineage masters. So today we're going to dive

00:01:28.400 --> 00:01:36.120
 deeply into the middle-wave view, which is in one way, just kind of by an honest assessment,

00:01:36.120 --> 00:01:41.080
 we're kind of showing up really late to the party. This has been taught by the Buddhist

00:01:41.080 --> 00:01:48.280
 Sakimuni for 2500 years ago, and it's continually been taught and practiced by this lineage

00:01:48.280 --> 00:01:54.720
 of masters, and it's actually perfect timing right now. We've all arrived to receive these

00:01:54.720 --> 00:02:00.240
 precious golden nugget teachings that have been preserved uninterruptedly without any

00:02:00.240 --> 00:02:06.240
 mistaken errors or kind of mixing in opinions and conceptualizations. So here we are, we

00:02:06.240 --> 00:02:10.680
 get to be together for a short little window of time and discuss something as profound

00:02:10.680 --> 00:02:17.600
 and vast as the middle-wave view, which is really the elixir of all the troubles we'll

00:02:17.600 --> 00:02:22.640
 ever experience and all the different suffering we've ever gone through. So we'll just take

00:02:22.640 --> 00:02:30.440
 a minute to pause and really like honor that, that we're really kind of midstream here.

00:02:30.440 --> 00:02:36.240
 Everything that we're doing here together is like because of the kindness and the perseverance

00:02:36.240 --> 00:02:42.480
 of these lineage masters, these elders and ancestors that have really persevered to fully

00:02:42.480 --> 00:02:48.960
 reveal their true nature. So that's why we have this opportunity now, and it's always

00:02:48.960 --> 00:02:53.560
 important to really reconnect with that lineage and the blessings of those masters and the

00:02:53.560 --> 00:03:00.140
 living lineage wisdom that they worked so hard to realize and also to preserve and continue

00:03:00.140 --> 00:03:06.440
 to make available for us now. So this is a really, really big topic, and we're going

00:03:06.440 --> 00:03:14.840
 to do kind of like a highlight reel, okay, of the Madhyamaka middle-wave view. So we'll

00:03:14.840 --> 00:03:23.800
 just jump right in. There's two approaches to the Buddha Dharma. They both have the same

00:03:23.800 --> 00:03:30.960
 purpose to reveal all obscurations and to totally remove these obscurations and fully reveal

00:03:30.960 --> 00:03:36.600
 our natural goodness qualities. So that's what all the teachings, 84,000 teachings of

00:03:36.600 --> 00:03:42.440
 the Buddha are designed to do, remove the temporary obscurations, the veils of ignorance

00:03:42.440 --> 00:03:47.880
 that are covering up our natural goodness, and to fully disclose or reveal the innate

00:03:47.880 --> 00:03:54.480
 goodness qualities we have. All the teachings are designed for this purpose. And there's

00:03:54.480 --> 00:04:01.040
 two general approaches towards these teachings, and one is the approach of the scholar, and

00:04:01.040 --> 00:04:06.640
 the other is the approach of the meditator. And both of these are legitimate paths, and

00:04:06.640 --> 00:04:11.600
 people of all types and varieties have taken both of these paths and achieved full enlightenment

00:04:11.600 --> 00:04:16.240
 and fruition by applying the techniques and the teachings according to their own dispositions,

00:04:16.240 --> 00:04:21.080
 whether they want to do a more scholarly approach or a more practice-oriented direct meditator

00:04:21.080 --> 00:04:29.080
 approach. So either of these paths are fully available to us. And as a ningma school, actually

00:04:29.080 --> 00:04:34.080
 we're asked by Gurumache and these lineage masters to always do both together. We call

00:04:34.080 --> 00:04:39.320
 this study and practice. We're honoring the scriptural lineage as well as the practice

00:04:39.320 --> 00:04:45.360
 or realization lineage. These always go hand in hand in the ningma school of Tibetan Buddhism.

00:04:45.360 --> 00:04:50.880
 And so it's not so much like a... It's something we'll always have to check in on both sides

00:04:50.880 --> 00:04:55.960
 of this. And what a scholastic approach generally does is starts more with what's outside, what's

00:04:55.960 --> 00:05:02.280
 more obvious, tangible, exterior, objective. And then looking closely, closely, closely,

00:05:02.280 --> 00:05:07.400
 it gets more and more inside till it kind of had the resounding question of like, how

00:05:07.400 --> 00:05:12.280
 is my subjective engagement, this knower, this awareness, how is it influencing what

00:05:12.280 --> 00:05:18.560
 is known, this appearance. So the scholastic approach is a little more gradual, but it's

00:05:18.560 --> 00:05:24.320
 also very thorough. We start outside with what's very obvious and tangible. We look

00:05:24.320 --> 00:05:30.600
 at it closely and gradually we come to investigate the looker, who's actually performing that

00:05:30.600 --> 00:05:39.120
 investigation. On the other hand, the meditator approach jumps directly into their own awareness.

00:05:39.120 --> 00:05:46.040
 How is my cognizance, my mind, this awareness, this consciousness, what is it? How does it

00:05:46.040 --> 00:05:52.680
 work? How does it influence experience? What is its nature? These are direct meditator

00:05:52.680 --> 00:05:58.680
 kind of questions or inquiries that we're... We have all these sets of teachings to jump

00:05:58.680 --> 00:06:03.490
 into and look for ourselves. The Buddha encouraged that. Both of these approaches to very

00:06:03.490 --> 00:06:04.100
 thoroughly

00:06:04.100 --> 00:06:10.240
 check what's going on here. So whether we're looking at what's outside, that's generally

00:06:10.240 --> 00:06:17.240
 called ontology being, a study of being of what is, or epistemology knowing, how do we

00:06:17.240 --> 00:06:22.760
 know what is. Either of these approaches are legitimate paths in Buddhism and they actually

00:06:22.760 --> 00:06:28.720
 go hand in hand. Ontology and epistemology, the study of being and knowing of the knower

00:06:28.720 --> 00:06:32.040
 and the known are always together.

00:06:32.040 --> 00:06:34.780
 In Buddhism in general, and in the Nyingma school in particular,

00:06:34.780 --> 00:06:38.200
 study and practice always go hand in hand.

00:06:38.200 --> 00:06:40.720
 So we can take either of these approaches.

00:06:40.720 --> 00:06:42.880
 And the great compassionate kindness teacher,

00:06:42.880 --> 00:06:46.520
 Buddha Shakyamuni, was so generous

00:06:46.520 --> 00:06:49.760
 in how he made the teachings available to us,

00:06:49.760 --> 00:06:53.000
 to our readiness, to our dispositions, to our faculties,

00:06:53.000 --> 00:06:55.680
 to our preferences, to our habits, to our biases,

00:06:55.680 --> 00:06:58.680
 to our prejudices, to our ways of being stuck

00:06:58.680 --> 00:07:00.720
 and way of being open.

00:07:00.720 --> 00:07:02.400
 He was so kind.

00:07:02.400 --> 00:07:04.400
 And they say there's three general phases

00:07:04.400 --> 00:07:06.320
 that the Buddha taught.

00:07:06.320 --> 00:07:10.540
 One is called the phase of no analysis.

00:07:10.540 --> 00:07:14.560
 The second is called the phase of slight analysis.

00:07:14.560 --> 00:07:19.200
 The third is called the phase of thorough analysis.

00:07:19.200 --> 00:07:21.520
 So at the first level of the Buddha's teachings,

00:07:21.520 --> 00:07:23.960
 the no analysis level, the Buddha just

00:07:23.960 --> 00:07:27.080
 agreed with what was commonly held to be true.

00:07:27.080 --> 00:07:31.400
 For example, there is suffering.

00:07:31.400 --> 00:07:33.560
 The Buddha said this is commonly held belief.

00:07:33.560 --> 00:07:36.760
 OK, I won't analyze that any further.

00:07:36.760 --> 00:07:38.920
 I'll agree, there's suffering.

00:07:38.920 --> 00:07:41.960
 So what are we going to do about it?

00:07:41.960 --> 00:07:44.960
 What is the cause?

00:07:44.960 --> 00:07:46.840
 Is it possible to fully remove suffering,

00:07:46.840 --> 00:07:48.400
 the cause of suffering?

00:07:48.400 --> 00:07:49.280
 What's the path?

00:07:49.280 --> 00:07:50.800
 What are the steps, the tools we have

00:07:50.800 --> 00:07:55.120
 to perform and engage to actually discover

00:07:55.120 --> 00:07:58.360
 the cessation of suffering?

00:07:58.360 --> 00:08:00.080
 This is the level of no analysis.

00:08:00.080 --> 00:08:02.480
 The Buddha just agreed with our worldly kind

00:08:02.480 --> 00:08:06.480
 of common, mundane ideas, what we consider common sense.

00:08:06.480 --> 00:08:08.960
 There is a person.

00:08:08.960 --> 00:08:11.360
 We're in a building.

00:08:11.360 --> 00:08:13.320
 The Buddha didn't challenge any of this.

00:08:13.320 --> 00:08:17.040
 He didn't-- no analysis, no further investigation

00:08:17.040 --> 00:08:20.040
 on this level of the teachings.

00:08:20.040 --> 00:08:24.200
 OK, the second level is called slight analysis.

00:08:24.200 --> 00:08:27.960
 And this is refuting our grasping onto the existence

00:08:27.960 --> 00:08:34.600
 of things like suffering, house, me, person, path,

00:08:34.600 --> 00:08:36.680
 enlightenment.

00:08:36.680 --> 00:08:40.120
 The Buddha did a slight analysis.

00:08:40.120 --> 00:08:45.200
 And he said, there is no such thing as true existence.

00:08:45.200 --> 00:08:46.320
 I don't truly exist.

00:08:46.320 --> 00:08:47.720
 You don't truly exist.

00:08:47.720 --> 00:08:49.120
 The path doesn't truly exist.

00:08:49.120 --> 00:08:50.920
 The house doesn't truly exist.

00:08:50.920 --> 00:08:55.480
 Enlightenment does not truly exist.

00:08:55.480 --> 00:09:00.320
 So the Buddha used conceptions to look more closely,

00:09:00.320 --> 00:09:04.040
 little more analysis, to help remove our grasping

00:09:04.040 --> 00:09:07.160
 onto this fixed tension.

00:09:07.160 --> 00:09:09.520
 We really believe these things are happening.

00:09:09.520 --> 00:09:11.280
 I'm suffering.

00:09:11.280 --> 00:09:13.200
 I need relief from suffering.

00:09:13.200 --> 00:09:14.480
 There's a bad thing happening.

00:09:14.480 --> 00:09:16.560
 There's a good thing I want.

00:09:16.560 --> 00:09:22.160
 The Buddha said, look closely, analyze, loosen.

00:09:22.160 --> 00:09:24.120
 Loosen the view.

00:09:24.120 --> 00:09:27.080
 Open the awareness.

00:09:27.080 --> 00:09:30.800
 Let a little more curiosity in.

00:09:30.800 --> 00:09:33.760
 Look a little more closely.

00:09:33.760 --> 00:09:36.720
 If we look really closely, we won't really

00:09:36.720 --> 00:09:42.680
 find a substantially existent permanent thing anywhere.

00:09:42.680 --> 00:09:46.880
 The idea of a singular, independent, permanent entity

00:09:46.880 --> 00:09:47.920
 is complete fiction.

00:09:47.920 --> 00:09:53.720
 Everything has parts.

00:09:53.720 --> 00:09:58.640
 Everything arises in dependence on other things.

00:09:58.640 --> 00:10:02.040
 And everything is impermanent.

00:10:02.040 --> 00:10:05.560
 Sip, singular, independent, permanent.

00:10:05.560 --> 00:10:10.160
 There's no such thing that exists in all of the universe.

00:10:10.160 --> 00:10:12.840
 If we think it, feel it exists, that's one thing.

00:10:12.840 --> 00:10:15.880
 If we look more closely, the little more analysis,

00:10:15.880 --> 00:10:17.840
 we won't be able to find that.

00:10:17.840 --> 00:10:20.760
 It is unfindable.

00:10:20.760 --> 00:10:22.520
 And that leads us to the third phase

00:10:22.520 --> 00:10:26.040
 of the Buddha's teaching, thorough analysis.

00:10:26.040 --> 00:10:27.800
 So at this phase, the Buddha wasn't just

00:10:27.800 --> 00:10:30.400
 saying use concepts to kind of understand,

00:10:30.400 --> 00:10:34.160
 having a better conceptual map, a more refined, intelligent kind

00:10:34.160 --> 00:10:41.080
 of way to argument or to kind of locate my experience.

00:10:41.080 --> 00:10:44.840
 But to actually be in non-conceptual wisdom

00:10:44.840 --> 00:10:49.840
 awareness, not duality consciousness,

00:10:49.840 --> 00:10:56.240
 not dualistic mind, not subject and object,

00:10:56.240 --> 00:10:58.600
 not a framework that has a me in here

00:10:58.600 --> 00:11:00.760
 and a something other than me out there,

00:11:00.760 --> 00:11:03.840
 a subject and an object.

00:11:03.840 --> 00:11:06.080
 Before that layer of filtering happens

00:11:06.080 --> 00:11:10.000
 in my own immediate experience, before that happens,

00:11:10.000 --> 00:11:14.400
 recognize how the mind is with prajna.

00:11:14.400 --> 00:11:19.000
 Wisdom, non-conceptual wisdom awareness.

00:11:19.000 --> 00:11:22.000
 Unborn, unceasing, by nature like the sky,

00:11:22.000 --> 00:11:24.440
 experienced by self-reflexive awarenesses,

00:11:24.440 --> 00:11:26.760
 discerning, pristine cognition.

00:11:26.760 --> 00:11:28.520
 This is the great master, Shantrakshita,

00:11:28.520 --> 00:11:31.920
 added to the beginning of the heart sutra.

00:11:31.920 --> 00:11:36.400
 It's pointing to the middle way view, the lived experience

00:11:36.400 --> 00:11:40.480
 of what it's like to be in non-conceptual wisdom

00:11:40.480 --> 00:11:41.400
 awareness.

00:11:41.400 --> 00:11:45.520
 This is the lived experience of the middle way view.

00:11:45.520 --> 00:11:49.240
 Unborn, unceasing, by nature like the sky,

00:11:49.240 --> 00:11:52.000
 experienced by self-reflexive awarenesses,

00:11:52.000 --> 00:11:55.800
 discerning, pristine cognition.

00:11:55.800 --> 00:11:58.920
 So this is the topic that we're discussing today,

00:11:58.920 --> 00:12:01.760
 the middle way view.

00:12:01.760 --> 00:12:05.800
 So if we look, take a kind of step back

00:12:05.800 --> 00:12:09.000
 from this no analysis, slight analysis, thorough analysis,

00:12:09.000 --> 00:12:13.800
 the ways that Buddha generally made his teachings a little

00:12:13.800 --> 00:12:17.160
 more direct to the true nature, the way enlightened beings

00:12:17.160 --> 00:12:19.640
 experience things, not the way deluded sentient beings,

00:12:19.640 --> 00:12:22.520
 like myself, experience things, the way enlightened beings

00:12:22.520 --> 00:12:26.840
 experience things, this first turning of the wheel of Dharma,

00:12:26.840 --> 00:12:31.520
 the four noble truths, cause and effect, interdependence.

00:12:31.520 --> 00:12:35.280
 That is this no analysis level.

00:12:35.280 --> 00:12:40.200
 The second turning is called rangtong, empty of self,

00:12:40.200 --> 00:12:44.440
 empty of fixed self, empty of fixed identity, rangtong.

00:12:44.440 --> 00:12:46.800
 These are the heart sutra teachings, the prajnaparamita

00:12:46.800 --> 00:12:50.440
 sutras that the Buddha gave.

00:12:50.440 --> 00:12:55.480
 This is slight analysis and thorough analysis.

00:12:55.480 --> 00:12:59.120
 The Buddha both said when we look closer,

00:12:59.120 --> 00:13:01.920
 nothing fits those conceptual frameworks.

00:13:01.920 --> 00:13:05.920
 Nothing truly exists in the way we feel it might.

00:13:05.920 --> 00:13:11.880
 If we look even closer, we'll pop into absolute awareness,

00:13:11.880 --> 00:13:15.200
 what we call prajna, non-conceptual wisdom

00:13:15.200 --> 00:13:18.520
 awareness, this is thorough analysis.

00:13:18.520 --> 00:13:21.320
 So in the Madhyamaka, our middleweight teachings,

00:13:21.320 --> 00:13:25.760
 this is saying the first part, slight analysis is going beyond

00:13:25.760 --> 00:13:30.880
 all-- sorry, slight analysis is lacking or empty

00:13:30.880 --> 00:13:35.040
 of intrinsic existence or inherent existence,

00:13:35.040 --> 00:13:37.480
 no fixed identity.

00:13:37.480 --> 00:13:40.720
 There is no such thing as a fixed property, identity,

00:13:40.720 --> 00:13:45.680
 pattern, person, place, thing.

00:13:45.680 --> 00:13:48.560
 That is mistaken belief.

00:13:48.560 --> 00:13:50.840
 It's just a false belief.

00:13:50.840 --> 00:13:54.160
 Those things don't exist.

00:13:54.160 --> 00:13:59.600
 Then the Buddha so kindly said, oh, we

00:13:59.600 --> 00:14:01.280
 might grasp onto non-existence.

00:14:01.280 --> 00:14:01.880
 They don't exist.

00:14:01.880 --> 00:14:02.480
 Nothing exists.

00:14:02.480 --> 00:14:05.840
 No eye, no ear, no nose, no tongue, no body, no mind.

00:14:05.840 --> 00:14:07.760
 So nothing.

00:14:07.760 --> 00:14:09.120
 The Buddha said, no.

00:14:09.120 --> 00:14:12.120
 Third turning-- or sorry, this is in the thorough analysis.

00:14:12.120 --> 00:14:16.560
 Look at, in your own awareness, how it functions when it's not

00:14:16.560 --> 00:14:17.680
 conceptualizing at all.

00:14:17.680 --> 00:14:19.080
 And this, the middleweight teachings,

00:14:19.080 --> 00:14:27.040
 say, going beyond conceptual designation, non-conceptual,

00:14:27.040 --> 00:14:30.960
 before conceptual layering happens, being wisdom.

00:14:30.960 --> 00:14:32.880
 It's called natural mind, ordinary mind.

00:14:32.880 --> 00:14:35.440
 There's different-- the Buddha taught so many ways about this.

00:14:35.440 --> 00:14:40.360
 Then the third turning teachings are,

00:14:40.360 --> 00:14:43.520
 what is it actually like when we experience

00:14:43.520 --> 00:14:45.000
 non-conceptual wisdom awareness?

00:14:45.000 --> 00:14:46.880
 What's that like?

00:14:46.880 --> 00:14:49.320
 What is it not?

00:14:49.320 --> 00:14:50.200
 But what is it like?

00:14:50.200 --> 00:14:56.280
 Then this is the third turning teachings.

00:14:56.280 --> 00:15:00.160
 Shintong, empty of other, empty of what's

00:15:00.160 --> 00:15:04.040
