 So I'll lay some more foundation.

00:22:15.800 --> 00:22:17.680
 The Buddha taught four philosophical schools.

00:22:17.680 --> 00:22:23.680
 And like all of these teachings we're going over

00:22:23.680 --> 00:22:26.240
 and the nine yanas according to the Nyingma school,

00:22:26.240 --> 00:22:28.240
 they all lead to another step.

00:22:28.240 --> 00:22:32.880
 It's called yarden, geared forward.

00:22:32.880 --> 00:22:38.080
 Each step, we're on it, leans us into the next step.

00:22:38.080 --> 00:22:41.440
 That step, we're on that, leans us into the next step.

00:22:41.440 --> 00:22:43.640
 They're geared to the next.

00:22:43.640 --> 00:22:46.640
 That's how the sequence of the nine yanas work.

00:22:46.640 --> 00:22:49.040
 They're not against each other.

00:22:49.040 --> 00:22:52.360
 It naturally extends into the next step.

00:22:52.360 --> 00:22:55.080
 Each subyana or subvehicle, sublevel,

00:22:55.080 --> 00:22:57.760
 it'll gradually open up into the next level

00:22:57.760 --> 00:23:01.440
 if we keep that inquiry going.

00:23:01.440 --> 00:23:03.960
 The Buddha said that's just how reality functions.

00:23:03.960 --> 00:23:08.200
 And each step is a little closer, a little more detailed,

00:23:08.200 --> 00:23:10.140
 a little more complete, a little more

00:23:10.140 --> 00:23:12.560
 expressive of the true nature of the middle way

00:23:12.560 --> 00:23:15.520
 view of how enlightened beings perceive things.

00:23:15.520 --> 00:23:16.720
 Each yana does that.

00:23:16.720 --> 00:23:19.840
 It's a little more directly from our own pristine valid

00:23:19.840 --> 00:23:21.280
 cognition.

00:23:21.280 --> 00:23:24.080
 And it's a little less relying on our distorted habitual

00:23:24.080 --> 00:23:25.840
 dualistic consciousness.

00:23:25.840 --> 00:23:28.720
 Each yana is higher that way, more inclusive.

00:23:28.720 --> 00:23:30.840
 It's greater.

00:23:30.840 --> 00:23:34.240
 It includes more of the true nature.

00:23:34.240 --> 00:23:37.360
 The techniques more directly jump us or pop us

00:23:37.360 --> 00:23:39.760
 into our true nature.

00:23:39.760 --> 00:23:41.400
 That's how the yana sequence works.

00:23:41.400 --> 00:23:49.240
 This first school is called Vibhashika,

00:23:49.240 --> 00:23:51.160
 great exposition school.

00:23:51.160 --> 00:23:53.440
 This is like a so-called foundational Buddhism

00:23:53.440 --> 00:23:55.600
 or Hinayana approach.

00:23:55.600 --> 00:23:57.440
 And there's many beliefs they hold.

00:23:57.440 --> 00:24:00.200
 But one belief they hold that I want to highlight here

00:24:00.200 --> 00:24:07.440
 is there are two things in life, mind and body.

00:24:07.440 --> 00:24:11.520
 Call it material, non-material.

00:24:11.520 --> 00:24:14.640
 And each of these are made up of two things.

00:24:14.640 --> 00:24:20.600
 Body is made up of irreducible particles of time

00:24:20.600 --> 00:24:27.620
 and irreducible particles of physical units of space.

00:24:27.620 --> 00:24:29.040
 That's matter.

00:24:29.040 --> 00:24:31.400
 Teeny, teeny, teeny, teeny, teeny, tiny,

00:24:31.400 --> 00:24:38.680
 cannot be split any further, units of time and space.

00:24:38.680 --> 00:24:42.640
 And then mind is made up of two things,

00:24:42.640 --> 00:24:52.040
 indivisible units of mind and the felt sense of self, me.

00:24:52.040 --> 00:24:54.800
 One is like, what actually is the mind?

00:24:54.800 --> 00:24:57.960
 These indivisible units of mind.

00:24:57.960 --> 00:24:59.880
 And what experience is that?

00:24:59.880 --> 00:25:04.460
 Me, my sense of me, felt sense of self.

00:25:04.460 --> 00:25:06.880
 The Vibhashika school, great exposition school,

00:25:06.880 --> 00:25:08.320
 believed this.

00:25:08.320 --> 00:25:12.680
 This is really close to like a contemporary modern science.

00:25:12.680 --> 00:25:14.680
 There's still the contemporary modern science.

00:25:14.680 --> 00:25:17.840
 We're looking for the smallest unit, the smallest particle

00:25:17.840 --> 00:25:21.160
 that makes up all of other aggregate reality.

00:25:21.160 --> 00:25:24.520
 Now it's contemporary to think of it as strings,

00:25:24.520 --> 00:25:28.040
 11 dimensional strings.

00:25:28.040 --> 00:25:29.400
 The Buddha said to keep looking.

00:25:29.400 --> 00:25:31.720
 And so the strings are going to dissolve too,

00:25:31.720 --> 00:25:32.800
 dissolve under analysis.

00:25:32.800 --> 00:25:35.160
 You'll find smaller units.

00:25:35.160 --> 00:25:36.880
 Keep looking, keep looking, keep looking.

00:25:36.880 --> 00:25:39.400
 Eventually we'll get to irreducible units

00:25:39.400 --> 00:25:44.120
 of time, space, mind, and a sense of self.

00:25:44.120 --> 00:25:46.080
 And that's everything that exists,

00:25:46.080 --> 00:25:48.480
 according to Vibhashika school.

00:25:48.480 --> 00:25:53.120
 This is way beyond what we see on the news

00:25:53.120 --> 00:25:56.360
 or what we talk about in our daily conversations.

00:25:56.360 --> 00:25:58.160
 And the Buddha said, you can experience this.

00:25:58.160 --> 00:26:01.640
 In the Pali tradition, it's called Bhanga.

00:26:01.640 --> 00:26:05.960
 The felt experience that you're just this vibrating aggregate

00:26:05.960 --> 00:26:11.040
 of indivisible particles can experience it.

00:26:11.040 --> 00:26:16.140
 So this is really much more subtle

00:26:16.140 --> 00:26:19.400
 than our typical ordinary average way of experiencing things.

00:26:19.400 --> 00:26:21.280
 Because it actually can be experienced,

00:26:21.280 --> 00:26:23.680
 not just theoretically asserted.

00:26:23.680 --> 00:26:26.920
 Or, you know, we haven't seen strings, you know.

00:26:26.920 --> 00:26:30.480
 They're all, it's like math, more or less math.

