 Sultrontica school, the Sutra school.

00:27:17.320 --> 00:27:20.880
 This is the Buddha taught.

00:27:20.880 --> 00:27:23.080
 The Buddha taught all these schools as our mind opens,

00:27:23.080 --> 00:27:24.760
 then the Buddha taught the next step,

00:27:24.760 --> 00:27:26.600
 geared forward to the next view.

00:27:27.600 --> 00:27:31.360
 The Sultrontica school, they kind of,

00:27:31.360 --> 00:27:34.720
 so there's so many points here, you can go over,

00:27:34.720 --> 00:27:36.040
 but like a fundamental distinction

00:27:36.040 --> 00:27:38.200
 between Sultrontica school and Vibhashika.

00:27:38.200 --> 00:27:42.840
 Sultrontica school, they think,

00:27:42.840 --> 00:27:45.440
 okay, so say there's these irreducible particles out there

00:27:45.440 --> 00:27:48.920
 of time and space and mind and sense of self.

00:27:48.920 --> 00:27:52.400
 That these little physical things out there,

00:27:52.400 --> 00:27:55.040
 we never directly perceive them.

00:27:55.040 --> 00:27:57.640
 How can mind perceive matter?

00:27:57.640 --> 00:28:00.180
 Because they're fundamentally different things.

00:28:00.180 --> 00:28:03.760
 Mind and matter are material and immaterial.

00:28:03.760 --> 00:28:06.720
 How can they ever understand each other or come in contact?

00:28:06.720 --> 00:28:09.880
 Because they're of different types.

00:28:09.880 --> 00:28:13.960
 Makes no sense for them to contact actually,

00:28:13.960 --> 00:28:16.440
 in Buddhist logic.

00:28:16.440 --> 00:28:19.280
 So what the Sultrontica school asserted

00:28:19.280 --> 00:28:23.440
 is that we never actually directly experience matter.

00:28:24.320 --> 00:28:28.380
 We only ever directly experience our image of matter.

00:28:28.380 --> 00:28:30.060
 Like there are these irreducible particles

00:28:30.060 --> 00:28:32.200
 that are so tiny you can never directly perceive them.

00:28:32.200 --> 00:28:33.320
 They're imperceptible.

00:28:33.320 --> 00:28:39.120
 But we only ever experience our cognition,

00:28:39.120 --> 00:28:42.360
 our mental overlay, our conceptual construction

00:28:42.360 --> 00:28:45.320
 of the matter.

00:28:45.320 --> 00:28:48.000
 Never directly experience matter, ever.

00:28:48.000 --> 00:28:51.440
 We just experience our projection.

00:28:53.560 --> 00:28:56.200
 All we ever experience is our projection.

00:28:56.200 --> 00:28:57.320
 That's the Sultrontica.

00:28:57.320 --> 00:29:03.780
 There are these little irreducible bits of space and time.

00:29:03.780 --> 00:29:07.020
 We never directly experience them.

00:29:07.020 --> 00:29:10.400
 We just have a generalized overlay

00:29:10.400 --> 00:29:13.380
