00:29:40.640 --> 00:29:42.760
 They don't believe in the Bhumis, the five past.

00:29:42.760 --> 00:29:45.220
 They refute three Kayas.

00:29:45.220 --> 00:29:46.640
 They don't believe in these higher teachings.

00:29:46.640 --> 00:29:49.040
 The Buddha didn't teach those in the sutras.

00:29:49.040 --> 00:29:52.200
 And these sutras that they're focusing on.

00:29:52.880 --> 00:29:57.880
 So then they're just following the words of the Buddha,

00:29:57.880 --> 00:30:00.080
 specifically the Sultrontica view.

00:30:00.080 --> 00:30:02.600
 They really didn't want to mix any other commentaries.

00:30:02.600 --> 00:30:04.080
 They just wanted to try to go directly

00:30:04.080 --> 00:30:05.480
 with the words of the Buddha.

00:30:05.480 --> 00:30:13.360
 And they only relied on very specific teachings of the Buddha.

00:30:13.360 --> 00:30:15.760
 They were more kind of available at that time.

00:30:15.760 --> 00:30:21.140
 So then what we get the next school

00:30:21.140 --> 00:30:25.000
 is called a Yogachara or Chitamatra or mind only.

00:30:25.000 --> 00:30:30.120
 So the next step here is worth taking this time

00:30:30.120 --> 00:30:32.120
 because we can do a really general thing here

00:30:32.120 --> 00:30:35.720
 and save some time if we know some certain key points.

00:30:35.720 --> 00:30:38.080
 I mean, in my view, that's my experience.

00:30:38.080 --> 00:30:40.000
 So Yogachara or mind only.

00:30:40.000 --> 00:30:45.960
 So Altrontica says all we ever experience is our projections.

00:30:45.960 --> 00:30:49.440
 It's called a representational theory of mind.

00:30:49.440 --> 00:30:51.500
 We only ever experienced a representation.

00:30:51.500 --> 00:30:53.460
 We never experienced the actual thing,

00:30:53.460 --> 00:30:55.640
 just our version of the thing.

00:30:55.640 --> 00:30:57.140
 That's all we ever experienced.

00:30:57.140 --> 00:31:00.560
 Yogachara or mind only says,

00:31:00.560 --> 00:31:05.360
 we assume there's a thing there that's being represented.

00:31:05.360 --> 00:31:08.160
 That's not true.

00:31:08.160 --> 00:31:11.260
 There's no thing there.

00:31:11.260 --> 00:31:18.120
 It's all projection through and through, mind only.

00:31:19.960 --> 00:31:22.140
 There is only mental.

00:31:22.140 --> 00:31:25.960
 So there's no kind of a big problem

00:31:25.960 --> 00:31:27.360
 of how mind and matter meet.

00:31:27.360 --> 00:31:28.680
 There's only mind.

00:31:28.680 --> 00:31:31.380
 It's all projection.

00:31:31.380 --> 00:31:35.320
 Mind only school.

00:31:35.320 --> 00:31:39.660
 I say, how could it all be mind?

00:31:39.660 --> 00:31:40.960
 How can mind interact with mind?

00:31:40.960 --> 00:31:42.240
 How can there be multiple minds?

00:31:42.240 --> 00:31:43.840
 'Cause we think so much were rooted

00:31:43.840 --> 00:31:46.320
 in these tangible material things, right?

00:31:46.320 --> 00:31:47.760
 I am.

00:31:47.760 --> 00:31:51.560
 But my thoughts influence each other all the time.

00:31:51.560 --> 00:31:52.760
 So do my emotions.

00:31:52.760 --> 00:31:55.280
 My anger leads to my hatred, leads to my jealousy,

00:31:55.280 --> 00:31:59.040
 leads to my hatred, leads to my self doubt.

00:31:59.040 --> 00:32:01.080
 This is a constant chain of mental things

00:32:01.080 --> 00:32:02.640
 influence each other all batting around

00:32:02.640 --> 00:32:04.000
 in the little cage up there.

00:32:04.000 --> 00:32:10.220
 Mind only school says it's only mind.

00:32:10.220 --> 00:32:12.840
 There's nothing out there, just mind.

00:32:12.840 --> 00:32:15.400
 That thing that we think is out there

00:32:15.400 --> 00:32:17.760
 causing our projection, it's not there.

00:32:17.760 --> 00:32:21.200
 That's a mistaken belief, misapprehension.

00:32:21.200 --> 00:32:25.740
 So mind only school has three big points.

00:32:25.740 --> 00:32:27.200
 They call the three natures.

00:32:27.200 --> 00:32:30.500
 One, imaginary nature.

00:32:30.500 --> 00:32:34.560
 Two, the dependent arising nature.

00:32:34.560 --> 00:32:40.100
 Three, the truly established nature.

00:32:40.100 --> 00:32:45.000
 (speaking in foreign language)

00:32:45.000 --> 00:32:48.920
 Imaginary nature is totally false 100%.

00:32:48.920 --> 00:32:50.320
 There's nothing that exists.

00:32:50.320 --> 00:32:51.720
 It's called, in common examples,

00:32:51.720 --> 00:32:55.100
 there's son of a barren woman, horn of a rabbit.

00:32:55.100 --> 00:32:57.220
 The other one's ego.

00:32:57.220 --> 00:33:00.440
 Ego is a completely false imaginary conception.

00:33:00.440 --> 00:33:05.400
 There's no actual referent in reality that that refers to.

00:33:05.400 --> 00:33:08.640
 It's completely false.

00:33:08.640 --> 00:33:09.680
 It's not a dream.

00:33:09.680 --> 00:33:13.000
 It's a totally wrong view.

00:33:13.000 --> 00:33:15.040
 There's no fixed entity.

00:33:15.040 --> 00:33:17.880
 The Sutra schools believe this,

00:33:17.880 --> 00:33:19.240
 and so does mind only schools.

00:33:19.240 --> 00:33:20.320
 So does Manyama school.

00:33:20.320 --> 00:33:25.320
 So does all the Bhadriyana schools, like the lineages.

00:33:25.320 --> 00:33:30.260
 That's imaginary.

00:33:30.260 --> 00:33:32.880
 So one, we have to remove the imaginary things.

00:33:32.880 --> 00:33:35.300
 The completely fictitious distortions we have

00:33:35.300 --> 00:33:37.800
 that have no actual coherence

00:33:37.800 --> 00:33:40.520
 with anything that's actually happening.

00:33:40.520 --> 00:33:43.880
 Like ego, sense of me, totally false.

00:33:43.880 --> 00:33:46.980
 The second dependent arising, okay,

00:33:46.980 --> 00:33:48.280
 we eliminate some of that.

00:33:48.280 --> 00:33:49.180
 What is happening?

00:33:49.180 --> 00:33:51.360
 Well, there's these things interacting with each other,

00:33:51.360 --> 00:33:52.320
 cause and effect.

00:33:52.320 --> 00:33:56.480
 There are apparent projections,

00:33:56.480 --> 00:34:00.480
 mental habits that are interplaying and causing results.

00:34:00.480 --> 00:34:09.040
 What are they happening in?

00:34:09.040 --> 00:34:12.680
 They say it's actually like the truly established nature.

00:34:12.680 --> 00:34:16.440
 In mind only school, this is called nondual mind.

00:34:16.440 --> 00:34:22.400
 In the path of mind only school,

00:34:22.400 --> 00:34:25.480
 what happens is nondual mind is more fully revealed

00:34:25.480 --> 00:34:30.140
 as our impure dependent arising nature is purified.

00:34:30.140 --> 00:34:35.120
 As our understanding of cause and effect gets more accurate

00:34:35.120 --> 00:34:39.060
 in the kind of totally false, artificial ways

00:34:39.060 --> 00:34:42.000
 we understand cause and effect are gradually removed,

00:34:42.000 --> 00:34:44.940
 then we get a purified experience,

00:34:44.940 --> 00:34:49.860
 which actually just means more natural, less obscured.

00:34:49.860 --> 00:34:51.880
 And then we fully reveal the,

00:34:51.880 --> 00:34:55.400
 we kind of have the finally established true nature.

00:34:55.400 --> 00:34:59.440
 100% unmistaken.

00:34:59.440 --> 00:35:02.340
 So they talk about this as the alaya being purified,

00:35:02.340 --> 00:35:05.080
 the ground, the swear house consciousness.

00:35:05.080 --> 00:35:06.720
 It has all these temporary delusions.

00:35:06.720 --> 00:35:08.040
 It's where all these experiences

00:35:08.040 --> 00:35:09.400
 since infinite beginningless time

00:35:09.400 --> 00:35:11.280
 have been stored as these habits.

00:35:11.280 --> 00:35:13.320
 Receives every single sense datum,

00:35:13.320 --> 00:35:15.960
 every percept, every concept, every perception,

00:35:15.960 --> 00:35:18.460
 every conception, inputs it there.

00:35:18.460 --> 00:35:20.840
 And then as the causes and conditions arise,

00:35:20.840 --> 00:35:22.440
 the habits are activated.

00:35:22.440 --> 00:35:24.840
 And then our projection is colored and textured

00:35:24.840 --> 00:35:27.160
 in certain ways based on what particular habits

00:35:27.160 --> 00:35:29.640
 are happening right now that we actually implanted

00:35:29.640 --> 00:35:34.340
 in our alaya consciousness a long time ago or more recently.

00:35:34.340 --> 00:35:37.920
 And gradually these distorted habits through practice,

00:35:37.920 --> 00:35:40.300
 they're not falsely reifying.

00:35:40.300 --> 00:35:42.960
 They're not falsely holding on to our experience.

00:35:42.960 --> 00:35:47.920
 These mistaken habits, the imaginary ones dissolve

00:35:47.920 --> 00:35:51.400
 and removed, then the mistaken cause and effect,

00:35:51.400 --> 00:35:55.640
 dependent arising habits are gradually removed

00:35:55.640 --> 00:35:56.480
 until they're gone.

00:35:56.480 --> 00:36:00.880
 And what's left is the truly established nature,

00:36:00.880 --> 00:36:01.800
 non dual mind.

00:36:04.000 --> 00:36:05.380
 That's a mind only school.

00:36:05.380 --> 00:36:10.620
 And then we get to the middle way view, Madhyamaka.

00:36:10.620 --> 00:36:20.900
 So the mind only school, or sorry, the middle way, Madhyamaka.

00:36:20.900 --> 00:36:24.820
 There's two, this is the Buddha taught

00:36:24.820 --> 00:36:27.600
 in a Prasamparamita sutras, the Madhyamaka.

00:36:27.600 --> 00:36:30.860
 It's commonly like distilled into the heart sutra teachings.

00:36:30.860 --> 00:36:32.720
 This is second turning.

00:36:32.720 --> 00:36:35.480
 Some people call it, some great masters call it.

00:36:35.480 --> 00:36:37.320
 The second turning is a direct teaching

00:36:37.320 --> 00:36:39.600
 of Prasamparamita of mind only.

00:36:39.600 --> 00:36:42.320
 Third turning is the hidden meaning of Prasamparamita.

00:36:42.320 --> 00:36:48.040
 Middle way view, what is the middle?

00:36:48.040 --> 00:36:54.460
 Oftentimes we think of middle as our left, right, middle.

00:36:54.460 --> 00:36:57.640
 Left, right, center.

00:36:57.640 --> 00:36:59.040
 This is not the middle way.

00:37:00.640 --> 00:37:03.220
 I think it's more helpful to think of left, right,

00:37:03.220 --> 00:37:05.040
 go up a level.

00:37:05.040 --> 00:37:09.520
 So it's up leveled into unmistaken awareness.

00:37:09.520 --> 00:37:10.780
 It's called prajna.

00:37:10.780 --> 00:37:13.800
 We're not playing the games of left and right,

00:37:13.800 --> 00:37:15.220
 of binary games.

00:37:15.220 --> 00:37:18.480
 It's not in dualistic consciousness anymore.

00:37:18.480 --> 00:37:20.720
 What the middle way view is pointing out

00:37:20.720 --> 00:37:24.000
 is unobstructed non dual wisdom awareness or prajna.

00:37:27.120 --> 00:37:30.960
 It's free from the extremes of playing all these games,

00:37:30.960 --> 00:37:34.600
 holding onto one side against the other side.

00:37:34.600 --> 00:37:39.000
 That's what mind only, or that's what middle way view

00:37:39.000 --> 00:37:40.600
 is trying to point us into,

00:37:40.600 --> 00:37:43.980
 trying to pop us into our natural intelligence

00:37:43.980 --> 00:37:45.980
 that's beyond the four extremes.

00:37:45.980 --> 00:37:52.760
 So their big critique of the mind only school

00:37:52.760 --> 00:37:55.680
 is mind only school, those really kind of adherence

00:37:55.680 --> 00:37:59.040
 to that view, they really believe in truly existent mind.

00:37:59.040 --> 00:38:02.080
 There is mind, it's happening right now.

00:38:02.080 --> 00:38:03.640
 This is all mind.

00:38:03.640 --> 00:38:05.080
 That's all there is, mind.

00:38:05.080 --> 00:38:10.240
 The Madhyamakans are the middle way practitioners.

00:38:10.240 --> 00:38:14.120
 There's two general types of Madhyamaka,

00:38:14.120 --> 00:38:15.920
 the verbal aspect or scripture,

00:38:15.920 --> 00:38:19.680
 and then the realization aspect or the meaning.

00:38:19.680 --> 00:38:24.720
 So there's all the teachings on Madhyamaka,

00:38:24.720 --> 00:38:27.060
 and then there's the actual direct experience

00:38:27.060 --> 00:38:28.200
 of those teachings.

00:38:28.200 --> 00:38:33.660
 So there's the theory, and then there's the experience.

00:38:33.660 --> 00:38:38.200
 And mind only was taught,

00:38:38.200 --> 00:38:40.780
 or you could say popularized by Nagarjuna,

00:38:40.780 --> 00:38:43.620
 'cause the Buddha taught mind only,

00:38:43.620 --> 00:38:44.760
 or sorry, I keep saying mind only.

00:38:44.760 --> 00:38:46.120
 The Buddha taught the middle way view.

00:38:46.120 --> 00:38:48.640
 The Buddha taught Santantika, Vibhachika,

00:38:48.640 --> 00:38:53.640
 mind only, middle way, all the Vajrayana.

00:38:55.720 --> 00:39:00.320
 But Nagarjuna popularized it, these middle way teachings.

00:39:00.320 --> 00:39:02.960
 And that became two streams.

00:39:02.960 --> 00:39:11.240
 The one stream was saying this,

00:39:11.240 --> 00:39:16.000
 more this simple way to put it.

00:39:16.000 --> 00:39:21.040
 One, okay, so if the main point of mind only

00:39:21.040 --> 00:39:23.400
 is to just be in a type of awareness

00:39:23.400 --> 00:39:25.880
 that doesn't play any binary games,

00:39:25.880 --> 00:39:30.960
 totally fluid and flexible, takes no fixed position,

00:39:30.960 --> 00:39:34.080
 non-dual wisdom awareness, the middle way.

00:39:34.080 --> 00:39:36.800
 That's what's being pointed out in the middle way teachings,

00:39:36.800 --> 00:39:38.360
 beyond conceptual designation.

00:39:38.360 --> 00:39:41.420
 There's two ways to do this.

00:39:41.420 --> 00:39:44.200
 One is we use relative stepping stones

00:39:44.200 --> 00:39:48.440
 to gradually introduce and reintroduce this in our mind.

00:39:48.440 --> 00:39:50.720
 The other is more sudden.

00:39:51.760 --> 00:39:56.360
 It says every conceptual position is fundamentally mistaken.

00:39:56.360 --> 00:39:59.540
 Don't play the games of concepts.

00:39:59.540 --> 00:40:03.200
 Just see the true nature, absolute truth.

00:40:03.200 --> 00:40:10.080
 So this stepping stone approach of the middle way view,

00:40:10.080 --> 00:40:12.400
 that is two subdivisions.

00:40:12.400 --> 00:40:15.960
 One, it says, you know, we're like people struggling here,

00:40:15.960 --> 00:40:17.740
 so like we need to use some relative truth.

00:40:17.740 --> 00:40:19.800
 You can't just refute all the relative positions

00:40:19.800 --> 00:40:21.880
 and say they're all wrong.

00:40:21.880 --> 00:40:22.800
 Which one's better?

00:40:22.800 --> 00:40:25.000
 Is there one that's better for a practitioner?

00:40:25.000 --> 00:40:28.040
 So there's the one that believes in the sutra school,

00:40:28.040 --> 00:40:32.640
 these irreducible particles, Sultrantika Madhyamaka.

00:40:32.640 --> 00:40:36.480
 And then there's one that uses more mind only school

00:40:36.480 --> 00:40:37.640
 on the relative level.

00:40:37.640 --> 00:40:40.640
 That's called Yogachara Madhyamaka, our mind only middle way.

00:40:40.640 --> 00:40:44.700
 That was expounded by the great master, Shantarakshita.

00:40:44.700 --> 00:40:47.860
 I said that was taught by also Gurumache.

00:40:49.200 --> 00:40:50.520
 That was what was brought,

00:40:50.520 --> 00:40:52.440
 that's how these teachings were brought to Tibet

00:40:52.440 --> 00:40:54.080
 in the eighth century.

00:40:54.080 --> 00:40:56.000
 Yogachara Madhyamaka.

00:40:56.000 --> 00:40:58.240
 These use relative stepping stones.

00:40:58.240 --> 00:41:01.280
 They engage what's happening on the relative phenomenal world.

00:41:01.280 --> 00:41:06.120
 What's the most helpful way according to these views?

00:41:06.120 --> 00:41:07.640
 One says irreducible particles.

00:41:07.640 --> 00:41:09.880
 There's all these tiny little bleeping things

00:41:09.880 --> 00:41:12.840
 that are making up these big aggregate things.

00:41:12.840 --> 00:41:15.200
 The other says, actually, it's just mind.

00:41:15.200 --> 00:41:17.960
 That's the relative.

00:41:17.960 --> 00:41:19.480
 That's the best relative description

00:41:19.480 --> 00:41:21.160
 that's most helpful to pop yourself

00:41:21.160 --> 00:41:23.000
 out of all conceptual designation

00:41:23.000 --> 00:41:24.820
 and recognize wisdom or awareness.

00:41:24.820 --> 00:41:27.680
 These are the gradual stepping stone approaches

00:41:27.680 --> 00:41:28.520
 of middle way.

00:41:28.520 --> 00:41:33.060
 The more direct one called Prasangaka Madhyamaka.

00:41:33.060 --> 00:41:36.060
 And what it does is it self-destructs every position.

00:41:36.060 --> 00:41:40.400
 And it doesn't do that by banging it with some other,

00:41:40.400 --> 00:41:44.000
 with our usual ways of conversing now,

00:41:44.000 --> 00:41:47.320
 which is basically to like hit people with bats.

00:41:48.960 --> 00:41:51.240
 This is degenerate age.

00:41:51.240 --> 00:41:54.840
 What Prasangaka Madhyamaka uses,

00:41:54.840 --> 00:41:56.920
 use the own logic of each position.

00:41:56.920 --> 00:41:59.000
 And if you keep using their logic,

00:41:59.000 --> 00:42:01.560
 eventually you get to a self-contradiction.

00:42:01.560 --> 00:42:03.160
 Reductio ad absurdum.

00:42:03.160 --> 00:42:05.400
 Every single relative position has that.

00:42:05.400 --> 00:42:10.860
 Every single one.

00:42:10.860 --> 00:42:13.880
 So, Nagarjan is famous for this tetralemma

00:42:13.880 --> 00:42:16.000
 that undoes the four extremes.

00:42:17.560 --> 00:42:22.120
 The extreme of this is, or this is not.

00:42:22.120 --> 00:42:25.280
 This both is and is not.

00:42:25.280 --> 00:42:27.400
 This neither is nor is not.

00:42:27.400 --> 00:42:29.760
 In logic terms, a, negation of a.

00:42:29.760 --> 00:42:31.360
 Both a and negation of a.

00:42:31.360 --> 00:42:33.680
 Neither negation, neither a and negation of a.

00:42:33.680 --> 00:42:37.280
 So these are the four logical positions

00:42:37.280 --> 00:42:41.400
 that it covers exhaustively all relative positions possible.

00:42:41.400 --> 00:42:44.260
 And Nagarjan taught, this is, they're all,

00:42:44.260 --> 00:42:46.440
 they all are limited, they're all diluted.

00:42:46.440 --> 00:42:48.980
 They're all fundamentally self-contradictory.

00:42:48.980 --> 00:42:51.040
 There's a thing, there's not the thing.

00:42:51.040 --> 00:42:52.560
 There's both a thing and not the thing.

00:42:52.560 --> 00:42:54.380
 There's neither thing nor not the thing.

00:42:54.380 --> 00:42:55.960
 They're all self-contradictory.

00:42:55.960 --> 00:42:59.420
 So when Nagarjan is fundamental wisdom of the middle way,

00:42:59.420 --> 00:43:02.620
 amongst other teachings, he refuted these thoroughly.

00:43:02.620 --> 00:43:04.980
 Why did he do that?

00:43:04.980 --> 00:43:06.640
 He said, don't play games

00:43:06.640 --> 00:43:09.300
 with conceptual relative designation.

00:43:09.300 --> 00:43:11.120
 They're all fundamentally flawed.

00:43:11.120 --> 00:43:13.180
 Just recognize absolute truth.

00:43:14.640 --> 00:43:18.720
 Be in the realized meaning of Madhyamaka.

00:43:18.720 --> 00:43:21.960
 Don't just play word games.

00:43:21.960 --> 00:43:25.680
 Don't just gradually use kind of distorted ideas

00:43:25.680 --> 00:43:27.760
 and less distorted until it's not distorted.

00:43:27.760 --> 00:43:31.760
 Just go right to undistorted, non-deceptive, absolute truth.

00:43:31.760 --> 00:43:33.840
 Don't play with fabrication, relative truth,

00:43:33.840 --> 00:43:36.240
 fabricated artificial reality.

00:43:36.240 --> 00:43:41.240
 Just ignite, turn on right now, wisdom awareness.

00:43:41.240 --> 00:43:44.280
 That's called absolute bodhichitta.

00:43:44.280 --> 00:43:46.160
 Just turn it on now.

00:43:46.160 --> 00:43:47.880
 Don't play all these gradual games.

00:43:47.880 --> 00:43:49.000
 There's too many beings suffering.

00:43:49.000 --> 00:43:51.220
 They need our help too much.

00:43:51.220 --> 00:43:52.400
 Just wake up.

00:43:52.400 --> 00:43:54.480
 Right?

00:43:54.480 --> 00:43:56.120
 Zen likes this approach.

00:43:56.120 --> 00:43:56.960
 Stick.

00:43:56.960 --> 00:44:00.120
 Just come out.

00:44:00.120 --> 00:44:01.040
 Wake up.

00:44:01.040 --> 00:44:04.800
 But then they use all these rituals and stepping stones

00:44:04.800 --> 00:44:06.720
 and you walk this way and clean the bowl this way

00:44:06.720 --> 00:44:07.560
 and all that.

00:44:07.560 --> 00:44:10.040
 That's all Svaatranthakam and Yamaka.

00:44:10.040 --> 00:44:13.160
 There's all kinds of conceptual supports.

00:44:14.280 --> 00:44:19.280
 So this is how, this comes down to the middle way view.

00:44:19.280 --> 00:44:27.920
 Say in one way, when Yamaka is,

00:44:27.920 --> 00:44:32.240
 if we're just looking at refuting inherent existence,

00:44:32.240 --> 00:44:37.080
 there's no fixed identity, that's conceptual.

00:44:37.080 --> 00:44:39.680
 'Cause we're still using concepts to realize that.

00:44:39.680 --> 00:44:43.640
 But then the direct meaning of Madhyamaka

00:44:43.640 --> 00:44:46.680
 is being in non-conceptual wisdom awareness or prajna,

00:44:46.680 --> 00:44:49.500
 not falling for any of these games.

00:44:49.500 --> 00:44:51.720
 Basically a way to say this is,

00:44:51.720 --> 00:44:55.080
 don't take any relative position as if it's absolutely true.

00:44:55.080 --> 00:45:00.540
 Because all relative positions are absolutely false.

00:45:00.540 --> 00:45:03.440
 They are all distorted.

00:45:03.440 --> 00:45:06.060
 The Buddha taught this so clearly.

00:45:06.060 --> 00:45:08.440
 Conceptual mind is fundamentally distorted.

00:45:08.440 --> 00:45:09.780
 The prayer of kunden sampo,

00:45:09.780 --> 00:45:13.080
 that's the big demon in Buddhism, conceptualization.

00:45:13.640 --> 00:45:18.640
 We can use concepts to get into un-conceptual

00:45:18.640 --> 00:45:21.880
 or non-conceptual meditation.

00:45:21.880 --> 00:45:24.080
 That's the stepping stone middle way approach.

00:45:24.080 --> 00:45:28.580
 Or we can just directly try to recognize

00:45:28.580 --> 00:45:30.120
 non-dual wisdom awareness.

00:45:30.120 --> 00:45:32.280
 That's the Prasangaka Madhyamaka approach.

00:45:32.280 --> 00:45:36.640
 That's Rangthong, empty of other, or sorry,

00:45:36.640 --> 00:45:39.360
 empty of self, empty of self-identity.

00:45:39.360 --> 00:45:41.840
 The great master, Kembo Sultram Jamsaramichhe says,

00:45:41.840 --> 00:45:45.520
 Prasangaka Madhyamaka is the ultimate highest view,

00:45:45.520 --> 00:45:48.880
 philosophically, because all relative positions

00:45:48.880 --> 00:45:50.640
 are fundamentally erroneous.

00:45:50.640 --> 00:45:54.920
 If you try to establish any relative position,

00:45:54.920 --> 00:45:57.360
 it will be mistaken.

00:45:57.360 --> 00:45:59.800
 So don't establish a relative position.

00:45:59.800 --> 00:46:01.700
 Abide in ultimate truth.

00:46:01.700 --> 00:46:05.480
 They don't affirm anything.

00:46:05.480 --> 00:46:07.540
 They just establish that relative positions

00:46:07.540 --> 00:46:09.440
 are fundamentally limited.

00:46:09.440 --> 00:46:11.760
 So don't play with limited duality mind.

00:46:11.760 --> 00:46:14.160
 Recognize unlimited duality,

00:46:14.160 --> 00:46:16.320
 unlimited non-dual wisdom awareness.

