 That's the basis of tantra.

00:49:09.560 --> 00:49:11.600
 That's why the Middleweight View of Madhyamika View,

00:49:11.600 --> 00:49:14.720
 the great Madhyamika View is non-dual wisdom awareness

00:49:14.720 --> 00:49:19.320
 or prajna, wisdom inseparable with compassion.

00:49:19.320 --> 00:49:21.520
 That's how this is the foundation of tantra.

00:49:21.520 --> 00:49:25.420
 The Middleweight View leans into tantra.

00:49:25.420 --> 00:49:29.000
 It's geared forward to tantra practice.

00:49:29.000 --> 00:49:32.120
 That's what we're doing at the beginning of every session.

00:49:32.120 --> 00:49:34.040
 That's what we're trying to reintroduce

00:49:34.040 --> 00:49:35.680
 in our sadhana practice to ourselves

00:49:35.680 --> 00:49:38.040
 to abide in the Middleweight View.

00:49:38.040 --> 00:49:39.920
 That's when dissolution happens.

00:49:39.920 --> 00:49:44.240
 That's called the Middleweight View, great Madhyamika.

00:49:44.240 --> 00:49:46.160
 It could be called zogchen, mahamudra,

00:49:46.160 --> 00:49:49.840
 prajna, paramitta, shije, chud, lamdre.

00:49:49.840 --> 00:49:51.720
 Ramachas have gone over this so many times.

00:49:51.720 --> 00:49:55.040
 This is just the Buddha nature happening unobstructedly.

00:49:55.040 --> 00:49:57.580
 So in the sutras, that's how they talk about it in the sutras,

00:49:57.580 --> 00:49:59.320
 unobstructed Buddha nature.

00:49:59.320 --> 00:50:02.240
 In the tantras, they talk about it as rigpa.

00:50:04.600 --> 00:50:06.600
 Or ordinary mind.

00:50:06.600 --> 00:50:08.840
 How the mind is when it's not funneled

00:50:08.840 --> 00:50:10.280
 through all these concepts.

00:50:10.280 --> 00:50:13.920
 And then a key point here is it's not dumbing down

00:50:13.920 --> 00:50:16.080
 the mind becoming pre-conceptual.

00:50:16.080 --> 00:50:17.820
 We're not trying to be like cows.

00:50:17.820 --> 00:50:24.240
 Post-conceptual, we're trying to use concepts when necessary

00:50:24.240 --> 00:50:27.480
 to skillfully communicate with others.

00:50:27.480 --> 00:50:31.480
 But to see, that's just one way of communicating.

00:50:31.480 --> 00:50:33.520
 There's all these other ways of communicating

00:50:33.520 --> 00:50:36.360
 that the Buddha pointed towards post-conceptual,

00:50:36.360 --> 00:50:42.240
 non-conceptual, wisdom awareness.

00:50:42.240 --> 00:50:44.840
 That's what the middle way view is pointing towards.

00:50:44.840 --> 00:50:49.460
 They do that by not establishing any fixed relative position.

00:50:49.460 --> 00:50:53.560
 They let every relative position undo itself.

00:50:53.560 --> 00:50:56.080
 And what's left isn't a smoldering wasteland

00:50:56.080 --> 00:50:58.540
 of extreme relativism.

00:50:58.540 --> 00:51:01.100
 What's left is non-dual wisdom awareness.

00:51:02.080 --> 00:51:06.240
 Wisdom, that's how Buddhism is very different

00:51:06.240 --> 00:51:07.480
 than deconstructionism.

00:51:07.480 --> 00:51:11.200
 In the end, what's left when you see

00:51:11.200 --> 00:51:14.200
 that everything's relative, wisdom's left.

00:51:14.200 --> 00:51:17.600
 That's why they say Buddhas don't have consciousness.

00:51:17.600 --> 00:51:19.000
 They only have wisdom.

00:51:19.000 --> 00:51:23.560
 That's why I talk about the five wisdoms.

00:51:23.560 --> 00:51:27.880
 Buddhas don't have conceptual mind.

