00:58:33.060 --> 00:58:33.900
 Look.

00:58:33.900 --> 00:58:36.880
 Look at it.

00:58:36.880 --> 00:58:38.660
 I challenge everyone.

00:58:38.660 --> 00:58:40.540
 Pre-integral worldviews.

00:58:40.540 --> 00:58:41.640
 This isn't an elitist thing.

00:58:41.640 --> 00:58:43.280
 It's not like Ata Yoga is the only good one

00:58:43.280 --> 00:58:44.520
 and all these other yanas are bad.

00:58:44.520 --> 00:58:46.520
 That's not saying anything like that.

00:58:46.520 --> 00:58:49.320
 Pre-integral worldviews,

00:58:49.320 --> 00:58:51.440
 the fundamental belief that they all have,

00:58:51.440 --> 00:58:53.920
 I'm right, everyone else is wrong.

00:58:53.920 --> 00:58:58.160
 It's part of the operating system.

00:58:58.160 --> 00:59:02.480
 The integral worldview is the only one that stops doing that.

00:59:02.480 --> 00:59:05.240
 And then after that, it doesn't make that mistake again.

00:59:06.560 --> 00:59:10.980
 Middleweight view is the only Buddhist view

00:59:10.980 --> 00:59:13.800
 that goes beyond fixating on relative views.

00:59:13.800 --> 00:59:17.960
 And it just works with other people's positions,

00:59:17.960 --> 00:59:19.440
 whatever's helpful to them.

00:59:19.440 --> 00:59:24.420
 This is the same middleweight view.

00:59:24.420 --> 00:59:26.320
 Integral worldview is the exact same.

00:59:26.320 --> 00:59:29.180
 Theory is a different thing.

00:59:29.180 --> 00:59:33.520
 Middleweight has theory, it has experience.

00:59:33.520 --> 00:59:36.440
 Every worldview has the theory, theoretical map.

00:59:36.440 --> 00:59:38.240
 Then it has the actual experience.

00:59:38.240 --> 00:59:43.040
 But you can't be a Bodhisattva really seriously

00:59:43.040 --> 00:59:45.280
 and think you're right and everyone's wrong.

00:59:45.280 --> 00:59:46.540
 That's impossible.

00:59:46.540 --> 00:59:47.640
 It doesn't fit.

00:59:47.640 --> 00:59:50.320
 'Cause Bodhisattva approach

00:59:50.320 --> 00:59:53.400
 fundamentally believes in the middleweight view.

00:59:53.400 --> 00:59:55.160
 Prajna is the only actual answer

00:59:55.160 --> 00:59:58.880
 because every other answer really believes it's right

00:59:58.880 --> 01:00:01.080
 and all the other ones are wrong.

01:00:01.080 --> 01:00:02.440
 So that's my challenge.

01:00:07.440 --> 01:00:10.000
 If we're really serious about being Bodhisattvas,

01:00:10.000 --> 01:00:12.280
 we really have to upend our view

01:00:12.280 --> 01:00:13.840
 that I'm right and you're wrong.

01:00:13.840 --> 01:00:17.900
 It's not good enough to just do longer treat

01:00:17.900 --> 01:00:19.380
 or say some prayers a little bit

01:00:19.380 --> 01:00:22.400
 and then come out and use our Buddhist jargon

01:00:22.400 --> 01:00:24.220
 and hang out with our Buddhist friends and all that.

01:00:24.220 --> 01:00:27.000
 The world needs more than that from us.

01:00:27.000 --> 01:00:30.360
 We're talking about things beyond self, beyond other,

01:00:30.360 --> 01:00:32.000
 beyond this ism and that ism

01:00:32.000 --> 01:00:34.440
 and this tradition and that tradition.

01:00:34.440 --> 01:00:36.360
 Buddhism needs a lot more flexible beings

01:00:36.360 --> 01:00:39.440
 and the middleweight view is that flexible approach.

01:00:39.440 --> 01:00:41.760
 That's essentially the Buddhist teaching.

01:00:41.760 --> 01:00:43.240
 If we're not doing middleweight view

01:00:43.240 --> 01:00:45.240
 and we think we're doing all this Vajrayana

01:00:45.240 --> 01:00:47.160
 Tibetan Buddhism, we're really not.

01:00:47.160 --> 01:00:49.040
 We're fooling ourselves.

01:00:49.040 --> 01:00:51.440
 If we do a lot of Tibetan Buddhist practice in the end,

01:00:51.440 --> 01:00:52.480
 it doesn't really help much.

01:00:52.480 --> 01:00:54.240
 We're not doing it right.

01:00:54.240 --> 01:00:56.640
 I know, I've not done it right for a long time.

01:01:02.960 --> 01:01:07.160
 It's a challenge not just as I'm right and you're wrong.

01:01:07.160 --> 01:01:09.520
 It's, are we really in a state of mind

01:01:09.520 --> 01:01:12.540
 that actually is so caring about others' positions

01:01:12.540 --> 01:01:16.800
 that we'll like see how they are right too.

01:01:16.800 --> 01:01:20.840
 But it doesn't mean they're the right in the same way.

01:01:20.840 --> 01:01:27.260
 Prasankaka Madhyamaka on relative conventional truth

01:01:27.260 --> 01:01:31.680
 still has a spectrum of mistaken conceptual truth,

01:01:31.680 --> 01:01:34.300
 conventional truth, and unmistaken.

01:01:34.300 --> 01:01:37.280
 They still make all these designations

01:01:37.280 --> 01:01:38.420
 on the relative truth.

01:01:38.420 --> 01:01:41.160
 It's not just all relative, anything goes.

01:01:41.160 --> 01:01:44.280
 It's so refined, the view.

01:01:44.280 --> 01:01:46.340
 They just think that's all fictitious.

01:01:46.340 --> 01:01:50.120
 It's all fake, but there's some that are more accurate fake.

01:01:50.120 --> 01:01:53.600
 Some are more helpful.

01:01:53.600 --> 01:01:55.520
 There's some are more helpful Cinderella stories

01:01:55.520 --> 01:01:57.440
 as Sogsar Kentsen Rinpoche says.

01:01:57.440 --> 01:02:00.600
 But they're all provisional.

01:02:01.680 --> 01:02:06.680
 So that's my long winded thing.

01:02:06.680 --> 01:02:11.800
 And I meant this to be a little longer.

01:02:11.800 --> 01:02:15.600
 I mean, I can't possibly like go talk about middleweight view

01:02:15.600 --> 01:02:18.000
 and not go through to all the other philosophical schools

01:02:18.000 --> 01:02:20.760
 and locate it within the Nanyana system.

01:02:20.760 --> 01:02:23.720
 It's not true, you know, it's easy to say it's all space,

01:02:23.720 --> 01:02:27.960
 you know, but so what, easy breezy, you know.

01:02:27.960 --> 01:02:30.180
 Words are so easy, but when the challenge happens,

01:02:30.180 --> 01:02:33.600
 if we're not really actually coming from a place of wisdom,

01:02:33.600 --> 01:02:35.960
 we just collapse into our most convenient

01:02:35.960 --> 01:02:37.620
 habitual conceptualization.

01:02:37.620 --> 01:02:41.360
 And we lock up, and we freeze, and we fight.

01:02:41.360 --> 01:02:45.680
 That's called samsara.

01:02:45.680 --> 01:02:48.520
 It's not enough anymore for 21st century Buddhas

01:02:48.520 --> 01:02:50.640
 to just use nice, funny words,

01:02:50.640 --> 01:02:52.520
 and then we just don't really do practice,

01:02:52.520 --> 01:02:54.680
 or we do some practice, but we just do it in a way

01:02:54.680 --> 01:02:56.060
 that's not really curious,

01:02:56.060 --> 01:02:58.520
 it's not really trying to undo itself,

01:02:58.520 --> 01:03:00.360
 it's just trying to get in the time.

01:03:00.360 --> 01:03:04.080
 And then 20 years goes by, and then we say,

01:03:04.080 --> 01:03:05.720
 oh, I'm not really better or something,

01:03:05.720 --> 01:03:08.080
 the Buddhas is wrong, and Dharma is wrong,

01:03:08.080 --> 01:03:09.480
 then we blame, blame, blame, blame,

01:03:09.480 --> 01:03:11.980
 and Benhamdha Kamuramichi has talked about this a lot.

01:03:11.980 --> 01:03:16.800
 We're trying to use this time to,

01:03:16.800 --> 01:03:18.740
 this is really preventative medicine.

01:03:18.740 --> 01:03:21.840
 We need to know some of these key points.

01:03:21.840 --> 01:03:26.740
 We need to know how mind-only school is based on

01:03:26.740 --> 01:03:28.560
 Swatranthaka, is based on Vibhachaka,

01:03:28.560 --> 01:03:31.560
 and it leads to middle way, which leads to Vatriyana,

01:03:31.560 --> 01:03:35.360
 which leads to Dzogchen, which goes beyond all isms.

01:03:35.360 --> 01:03:40.220
 It's not about any system, it's just about naturalness.

01:03:40.220 --> 01:03:43.640
 But we need to clearly see with mindfulness

01:03:43.640 --> 01:03:47.720
 how we're not doing that, and we need to be kind to ourself

01:03:47.720 --> 01:03:51.600
 to see how we're not doing that, not to say, I'm perfect.

01:03:51.600 --> 01:03:55.800
 See how I keep messing up, if I'm not willing to look

01:03:55.800 --> 01:03:58.760
 at my unconscious habits, or not to ask for help,

01:03:58.760 --> 01:04:03.440
 then they're just gonna keep being the background radiation,

01:04:03.440 --> 01:04:05.400
 the operating system I just don't see,

01:04:05.400 --> 01:04:08.940
 but usually everyone else sees, and it's just forever,

01:04:08.940 --> 01:04:11.240
 and we're gonna do this samsara thing forever.

01:04:11.240 --> 01:04:15.580
 But without mind-only school, Vatriyana's a joke.

01:04:15.580 --> 01:04:19.680
 We're gonna transform all this into a mandala

01:04:19.680 --> 01:04:21.760
 that makes no sense if there's actual

01:04:21.760 --> 01:04:23.000
 physical things out there.

01:04:25.340 --> 01:04:28.480
 If we're gonna go into all this, everything arises,

01:04:28.480 --> 01:04:30.080
 there's a hyung, so there's a syllable,

01:04:30.080 --> 01:04:33.680
 which becomes a ornament, like a certain hand object,

01:04:33.680 --> 01:04:35.480
 which becomes a deity, which becomes a retinue,

01:04:35.480 --> 01:04:37.240
 which does all these activities, and eneminate,

01:04:37.240 --> 01:04:39.720
 and gather, and dissolve, and then receive blessing,

01:04:39.720 --> 01:04:41.540
 and then open awareness.

01:04:41.540 --> 01:04:42.820
 We're gonna talk about doing all that.

01:04:42.820 --> 01:04:45.360
 How could a fixed position be true,

01:04:45.360 --> 01:04:47.440
 and have that practice make any sense?

01:04:47.440 --> 01:04:51.040
 It doesn't make any sense.

01:04:51.040 --> 01:04:55.160
 I mean, it's the only way to really be in a state

01:04:55.160 --> 01:04:56.520
 of mind that doesn't fixate.

01:04:56.520 --> 01:05:00.920
 That's what we're practicing, how to not fixate,

01:05:00.920 --> 01:05:03.920
 how to be present and engaged with appearance

01:05:03.920 --> 01:05:07.880
 that's totally flexible, empty of being fixated,

01:05:07.880 --> 01:05:10.020
 not really a non-reified experience.

01:05:23.340 --> 01:05:25.600
 That's the only way to freedom.

01:05:25.600 --> 01:05:28.020
 This is the only way we can really be of benefit to others,

01:05:28.020 --> 01:05:31.160
 is really see how we keep trapping ourselves,

01:05:31.160 --> 01:05:36.160
 and actually put the time in to unlock our own blockages.

01:05:36.160 --> 01:05:38.000
 No one can do it for us.

01:05:38.000 --> 01:05:41.240
 We have everything we need to do this now,

01:05:41.240 --> 01:05:44.080
 but it takes time to digest it,

01:05:44.080 --> 01:05:45.720
 and it takes time to chew on it,

01:05:45.720 --> 01:05:47.240
 and it takes time to engage it,

01:05:47.240 --> 01:05:49.240
 and it takes vulnerability and honesty to say

01:05:49.240 --> 01:05:50.920
 when I don't know what's going on,

01:05:50.920 --> 01:05:54.480
 and I need help, and to try to be vulnerable and receive help,

01:05:54.480 --> 01:05:58.280
 and to recognize some people are way farther along the path,

01:05:58.280 --> 01:06:01.220
 and to use their guidance, and to try our best,

01:06:01.220 --> 01:06:03.740
 and then we mess up, and then we try, try again.

01:06:03.740 --> 01:06:09.080
 And at the end of that, we're gonna be free,

01:06:09.080 --> 01:06:14.580
 and then we can really help beings, really help beings.

01:06:17.160 --> 01:06:20.860
 Exactly how it makes sense to them,

01:06:20.860 --> 01:06:23.420
 not how we think they need to be helped,

01:06:23.420 --> 01:06:28.820
 but really on their own side,

01:06:28.820 --> 01:06:30.960
 what makes them a little more open?

01:06:30.960 --> 01:06:35.820
 We need the flexibility to see the real nuggets of truth

01:06:35.820 --> 01:06:37.920
 in all of these positions,

01:06:37.920 --> 01:06:39.740
 and at the same time see how they're all limited,

01:06:39.740 --> 01:06:41.580
 they're all partial.

01:06:41.580 --> 01:06:44.120
 Everything's partially true on the relative level.

01:06:44.120 --> 01:06:45.480
 It's partially false.

01:06:47.220 --> 01:06:49.340
 So this wisdom awareness of prajna,

01:06:49.340 --> 01:06:51.220
 the only way to be that flexible,

01:06:51.220 --> 01:06:53.980
 that's the only way we can be flexible enough.

01:06:53.980 --> 01:06:55.800
 Then when we're that flexible,

01:06:55.800 --> 01:06:57.980
 we really can engage partial positions

01:06:57.980 --> 01:07:01.440
 with a lot of love and tenderness and care and respect.

01:07:01.440 --> 01:07:08.880
 Otherwise we're doing this Vajrayana thing for ourselves,

01:07:08.880 --> 01:07:09.920
 it's a disaster.

01:07:09.920 --> 01:07:15.940
 I'm doing Vajrayana so I can get free.

01:07:16.820 --> 01:07:17.660
 Good luck.

01:07:17.660 --> 01:07:20.580
 Doesn't work like that.

01:07:20.580 --> 01:07:23.900
 All the philosophical schools

01:07:23.900 --> 01:07:26.480
 already refuted the existence of itself.

01:07:26.480 --> 01:07:31.100
 We can't use all these high-end Buddhist teachings

01:07:31.100 --> 01:07:33.580
 and use them from a non-Buddhist world view,

01:07:33.580 --> 01:07:35.980
 believing in all these fixed entities.

01:07:35.980 --> 01:07:38.940
 This doesn't work, it won't work,

01:07:38.940 --> 01:07:40.860
 like Zog sarkhan Sarimache also says.

01:07:40.860 --> 01:07:43.180
 If you really want to use Buddhism to just be happy

01:07:43.180 --> 01:07:45.580
 and free-flowing and stuff, just get a massage.

01:07:47.820 --> 01:07:49.540
 It makes more sense.

01:07:49.540 --> 01:07:54.300
 We're doing it to be free, not to be happy.

01:07:54.300 --> 01:07:57.620
 Then it comes in, the great blissfulness

01:07:57.620 --> 01:07:59.340
 and nature's already great bliss.

01:07:59.340 --> 01:08:02.260
 So then it's like way past happiness.

01:08:02.260 --> 01:08:05.300
 But we actually have to be in that

01:08:05.300 --> 01:08:06.700
 and not just talk about that.

01:08:06.700 --> 01:08:11.820
 So that's my kind of going through the whirlwind

01:08:11.820 --> 01:08:16.100
 of all the Nanyanas in the four philosophical schools

01:08:16.100 --> 01:08:18.100
 to try to more firmly or clearly establish

01:08:18.100 --> 01:08:20.540
 what a middle-wave view might look like,

01:08:20.540 --> 01:08:21.860
 what it might be pointing towards.

01:08:21.860 --> 01:08:23.700
 So this is all just moon pointing.

01:08:23.700 --> 01:08:27.780
 And now we'll just kind of like use that moon pointing

01:08:27.780 --> 01:08:32.140
 to just relax in our practice.

01:08:32.140 --> 01:08:33.200
 So thanks so much.

01:08:33.200 --> 01:08:34.660
 Thanks to your patience for a little bit

01:08:34.660 --> 01:08:38.080
 of a kind of longer talk, but I appreciate you.

01:08:38.080 --> 01:08:39.060
 Thank you.

01:08:39.060 --> 01:08:39.900
 Thank you all.

01:08:46.100 --> 01:08:51.100
 Thank you, friends.

01:08:51.100 --> 01:09:04.780
 Thank you.

01:09:04.780 --> 01:09:06.100
 Thank you.

01:09:06.100 --> 01:09:07.660
 Thank you.

01:09:07.660 --> 01:09:09.140
 Thank you.

01:09:09.140 --> 01:09:11.820
 It's such a pleasure to be here with you all.

01:09:12.800 --> 01:09:16.720
 And yeah, we all have everything in our favor now.

01:09:16.720 --> 01:09:21.300
 Beautiful human beings, beautiful opportunity,

01:09:21.300 --> 01:09:23.860
 beautiful teachings, beautiful teacher,

01:09:23.860 --> 01:09:26.580
 beautiful path, beautiful sangha.

01:09:26.580 --> 01:09:28.860
 We really have everything.

01:09:28.860 --> 01:09:31.020
 It's all laid out for us.

01:09:31.020 --> 01:09:34.620
 And so we just, wherever we are, that's where we start.

01:09:34.620 --> 01:09:36.220
 That's where we continue.

01:09:36.220 --> 01:09:40.820
 And we just keep relaxing, keep resting,

01:09:40.820 --> 01:09:42.860
 keep engaging with a really joyful heart,

01:09:42.860 --> 01:09:44.580
 with really good intention.

01:09:44.580 --> 01:09:46.280
 Give others the benefit of the doubt.

01:09:46.280 --> 01:09:49.380
 Try to see their good, their really goodness first.

01:09:49.380 --> 01:09:55.420
 Then we can have a discussion about kind of finer points

01:09:55.420 --> 01:09:58.500
 that are harder to figure out, a little more complicated.

01:09:58.500 --> 01:10:00.780
 But like try to really start with really,

01:10:00.780 --> 01:10:03.320
 oh, you're a good being.

01:10:03.320 --> 01:10:06.900
 I'm a good being, you're a good being.

01:10:06.900 --> 01:10:08.820
 I'm like, we really are in this together.

01:10:08.820 --> 01:10:11.300
 We need to work together with that.

01:10:11.300 --> 01:10:14.020
 And we need to be really kind of discerning

01:10:14.020 --> 01:10:16.320
 about what we're bringing to the conversation,

01:10:16.320 --> 01:10:18.020
 about what my mind's doing,

01:10:18.020 --> 01:10:19.420
 what my habits are doing to me,

01:10:19.420 --> 01:10:21.940
 how they're helping me, how they're hurting me,

01:10:21.940 --> 01:10:24.580
 how they're helping and hurting others too.

01:10:24.580 --> 01:10:27.020
 So that's just being a responsible practitioner

01:10:27.020 --> 01:10:28.020
 of the Buddha Dharma.

01:10:28.020 --> 01:10:30.740
 And then this summary,

01:10:30.740 --> 01:10:33.220
 I thought to give a quick summary,

01:10:33.220 --> 01:10:34.860
 to just tie it all together,

01:10:34.860 --> 01:10:38.180
 which is a very succinct first point.

01:10:39.340 --> 01:10:40.940
 Everything is impermanent.

01:10:40.940 --> 01:10:47.020
 All boils down to these tiny irreducible particles

01:10:47.020 --> 01:10:48.600
 of space, time and mind.

01:10:48.600 --> 01:10:51.220
 That's by Bhashika.

01:10:51.220 --> 01:10:56.760
 All we ever experience is our projection.

01:10:56.760 --> 01:11:01.180
 That is Sultantika.

01:11:01.180 --> 01:11:05.760
 There is only projection.

01:11:08.620 --> 01:11:09.760
 That's mind only.

01:11:09.760 --> 01:11:17.900
 Some projections are really convenient useful placeholders

01:11:17.900 --> 01:11:22.900
 to recognizing what is beyond projection,

01:11:22.900 --> 01:11:26.460
 what is not filtered through

01:11:26.460 --> 01:11:29.080
 fundamentally deceptive projection.

01:11:29.080 --> 01:11:36.320
 That's called Categorized Middleweight View.

01:11:39.500 --> 01:11:44.500
 All projections are fundamentally distorted and diluted.

01:11:44.500 --> 01:11:48.780
 So just jump into what is fundamentally undistorted

01:11:48.780 --> 01:11:50.500
 and not diluted.

01:11:50.500 --> 01:11:53.300
 Pristine Wisdom Awareness, Prashna.

01:11:53.300 --> 01:11:59.740
 It's called uncategorized Middleweight View, Prasangika.

01:11:59.740 --> 01:12:06.660
 When we abide in pristine valid cognition

01:12:06.780 --> 01:12:11.780
 of the noble ones, then we use skillful means

01:12:11.780 --> 01:12:17.300
 to gradually refine our perceptions

01:12:17.300 --> 01:12:19.200
 and habits of body and speech.

01:12:19.200 --> 01:12:22.900
 This is Outer Tantras.

01:12:22.900 --> 01:12:31.920
 Outside in body, everything we see form, sound, space,

01:12:31.920 --> 01:12:36.180
 there is nothing impure.

01:12:36.180 --> 01:12:40.660
 It's all deities doing Dharma activities,

01:12:40.660 --> 01:12:44.100
 enlightened activities in a mandala, Maha Yoga.

01:12:44.100 --> 01:12:51.220
 Everything inside is just the activities of deities

01:12:51.220 --> 01:12:54.420
 in the mandalas which fundamentally make up

01:12:54.420 --> 01:12:58.780
 our Vajrabhadi, Salong Tigle, Anu Yoga.

01:12:58.780 --> 01:13:04.780
 Everything outside, inside, conceptual mind,

01:13:04.780 --> 01:13:09.220
 non-conceptual wisdom, has always only ever been

01:13:09.220 --> 01:13:11.360
 pristine, valid cognition.

01:13:11.360 --> 01:13:13.800
 It will never be stained.

01:13:13.800 --> 01:13:16.740
 It has never been broken.

01:13:16.740 --> 01:13:19.920
 It will always be 100% perfect and pure.

01:13:19.920 --> 01:13:23.300
 This is Ahti Yoga, Sogchen.

01:13:23.300 --> 01:13:29.460
 Then when it comes down to it, Venerable Kenshin,

01:13:29.460 --> 01:13:32.340
 Paul Dinscher, Barimba Che said in his glorious book,

01:13:32.340 --> 01:13:33.880
 The Nine Golden Chariots,

01:13:35.780 --> 01:13:39.080
 the closer we look at relative truth,

01:13:39.080 --> 01:13:43.240
 the more uncertain we become.

01:13:43.240 --> 01:13:48.100
 'Cause relative truth is fabricated

01:13:48.100 --> 01:13:51.720
 and fundamentally diluted.

01:13:51.720 --> 01:13:57.780
 The closer we look at absolute ultimate truth,

01:13:57.780 --> 01:14:00.020
 the more certain we become.

01:14:02.140 --> 01:14:05.720
 Because Prajna is unmistaked, unmistaken.

01:14:05.720 --> 01:14:10.880
 Perfect, pristine, valid cognition.

